roducer || [[TriStar Pictures]]\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Role\n! First aired\n! Last aired\n! Season\n! Episode(s)\n! Co-production\n! Network\n! Notes\n|-\n\n| ''[[Future Man (TV series)|Future Man]]'' || Executive producer || {{dts|2017|11|14}} || {{dts|2020|04|03}} || [[Future Man (TV series)#Season|2]] || [[Future Man (TV series)#Episodes|26]] || [[Point Grey Pictures|Point Grey Television]]<br>Matt Tolmach Productions<br>Turkeyfoot Productions<br>[[Sony Pictures Television]] || [[Hulu]] ||\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tolmach, Matt}}\n[[Category:American film producers]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:American Jews]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Beloit College alumni]]\n\n\n{{US-film-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Producer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = \n| image         = Matt Tolmach (7001175701).jpg\n| caption       = Matt Tolmach speaking at the 2012 WonderCon in Anaheim, California.\n| birth_name    = Matthew Tolmach\n| birth_date    = {{birth year and age|1964}}\n| birth_place   = [[New York City, New York]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = United States\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Film producer\n| education     = Beloit College\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| parents       = Judith Jaffe Tolmach Silber\n| spouse        = Paige Goldberg\n| family        = [[Sam Jaffe (producer)|Sam Jaffe]] (grandfather)<br> [[Adeline Schulberg]] (great-aunt)<br> [[B.P. Schulberg]] (great-uncle)\n}}\n\n'''Matthew Tolmach''' (born 1964)<ref name=DeadlineExit>[http://deadline.com/2010/10/matt-tolmach-discusses-his-sony-pictures-prexy-exit-to-produce-spider-man-80070/ Deadline: \"Matt Tolmach Discusses Exit As Sony Pics Prez And Segue To Producing 'Spider-Man'\" by Mike Fleming Jr] October 29, 2010</ref> is an American [[film producer]] and former co-president of production at [[Sony Pictures Entertainment]].\n\n==Biography==\nTolmach first became interested in film after hearing stories from his grandfather, producer and film executive [[Sam Jaffe (producer)|Sam Jaffe]].<ref name=DeadlineExit /> He is of [[Jewish]] descent. After moving to Los Angeles, he landed a job with [[Frank Marshall (producer)|Frank Marshall]] to make a documentary about Lance Armstrong that was directed by [[Alex Gibney]].<ref name=DeadlineExit /> In 2008, he was named co-president of production at [[Sony Pictures Entertainment]] with [[Doug Belgrad]] (whom he had been working with since 2003) where he managed the Spider-Man franchise.<ref name=DeadlineExit /><ref name=HollyRepSteps>Borys Kit [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/blogs/heat-vision/matt-tolmach-steps-down-columbia-33676 Matt Tolmach Steps Down From Columbia Pictures to Produce Spider-Man] hollywoodreporter.com, Retrieved on November 27, 2013</ref><ref name=MovCityTran>{{cite web|url=http://moviecitynews.com/2010/10/longtime-columbia-pictures-chiefs-matt-tolmach-and-doug-belgrad-transition-into-new-roles/|title=Longtime Columbia Pictures Chiefs Matt Tolmach And Doug Belgrad Transition Into New Roles|website=Moviecitynews.com|accessdate=November 27, 2013}}</ref> In 2010, he left Sony Pictures Entertainment to produce the next installment of ''[[Spider-Man]]''.<ref name=HollyRepSteps /><ref name=MovCityTran /> Belgrad was named as sole president of the studio and Hanna Minghella was named president of production.<ref name=HollyRepSteps /><ref name=MovCityTran />\n\n==Personal life==\nTolmach is married to director Paige Goldberg.<ref name=DeadlineHaunts>[http://deadline.com/2017/10/what-haunts-us-sexual-predator-documentary-filmmaker-says-we-can-stop-this-from-happening-1202193031/ Deadline: \"\u2018What Haunts Us\u2019 Documentary Director On Sexual Predators: \u201cWe Can Stop This From Happening\u201d\" by Anita Busch] October 23, 2017</ref> They have one child.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Production company\n! Distributor\n! Notes\n|-\n\n| 1993 || ''[[Money for Nothing (1993 film)|Money for Nothing]]'' || Producer || [[Hollywood Pictures]] || [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Buena Vista Pictures Distribution]] ||\n|-\n| 1995 || ''[[Coldblooded (film)|Coldblooded]]'' || Producer || [[PolyGram Filmed Entertainment]]<br>[[Propaganda Films]] || [[IRS Media]] ||\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film)|The Amazing Spider-Man]]'' || Producer || [[Columbia Pictures]]<br>[[Marvel Entertainment]]<br>[[Laura Ziskin|Laura Ziskin Productions]]<br>[[Avi Arad|Arad Productions, Inc.]]<br>Matt Tolmach Productions || [[Sony Pictures Entertainment|Sony Pictures Releasing]] ||\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[The Armstrong Lie]]'' || Producer || [[The Kennedy/Marshall Company|Kennedy/Marshall Productions]]<br>Jigsaw Productions<br>Matt Tolmach Productions || [[Sony Pictures Classics]] || \n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man 2]]'' || Producer || Columbia Pictures<br>Marvel Entertainment<br>Arad Productions, Inc.<br>Matt Tolmach Productions || rowspan=\"12\" |Sony Pictures Releasing ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Freaks of Nature (film)|Freaks of Nature]]'' || Producer || Columbia Pictures<br>[[LStar Capital]] || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Sausage Party]]'' || || Columbia Pictures<br>[[Annapurna Pictures]]<br>[[Point Grey Pictures]]<br>[[Nitrogen Studios]] || Special thanks\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2017 || ''[[Rough Night]]'' || Producer || Columbia Pictures<br>LStar Capital<br>Matt Tolmach Productions<br>Paulilu Productions ||\n|-\n| ''[[Spider-Man: Homecoming]]'' || Executive Producer || Columbia Pictures<br>[[Marvel Studios]]<br>[[Amy Pascal|Pascal Pictures]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle]]'' || Producer || Columbia Pictures<br>Matt Tolmach Productions<br>[[Dwayne Johnson|Seven Bucks Productions]]<br>[[Radar Pictures]] ||\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Venom (2018 film)|Venom]]'' || Producer || Columbia Pictures<br>Marvel Entertainment<br>[[Tencent Pictures]]<